<br>
The real change here, is wizard, and not only to manaburn.<br>
<br>
I have been on relatively hard raids, and a good strategy our wizard would employ, is to manaburn a very high hp mob at the beginning of the encounter, and rod back all their mana, and keep nuking for awesome dmg, rodding as needed.<br>
<br>
The manaburn nerf, and the mod rod nerf, just easily halved a guilds wizards firepower. On high end luclin mob I can only imagine the effect of going from 30 minutes fight with manaburning, mod rodding wizards, to melee for the biggest dmg part, considering those mobs have insane AC. Wizard had become awesome dmg for those fights.<br>
<br>
I am not saying that wizard did all the dmg, or that they were the sole source, but the mod rod change affects them even more then the cleric when it comes to class definition.<br>
<br>
Dmg on those fight will be dramatically reduced, healing will be limited to the amount of cleric you have, and remember, a druid who cast a 400 mana heal isn't nuking, and all those aa points spent in SCM is for naught if they are healing because the cleric can't keep up the heals.<br>
<br>
I'd say the average raid just lost a tremendous amount of dmg due to this forecoming change.<br>
<br>
Presently, cleric, druid, wizard depended heavilly on mages mod rod to do an awesome job.<br>
<br>
Without mod rod, or actually relying on the mediocre version now available, and no more stocking up by all your melee to be dropped before the big fight, you've just (exagerating here possibly) trippled your needed clerics for an encounter.<br>
<br>
In the long run, its not a single class thats getting the shaft, its the majority of small guild raiders who maximised mod rods, and key classes to achieve an end with fewer numbers.<br>
<br>
Every raiding guild, on every server has just been slowed down by a very harsh margin.<br>
<br>
